inclusion criteria: Criteria for inclusion of the mothers were: (i) to be resident in one of the study areas, (ii) to be at least 16 years old, (iii) to have a singleton pregnancy, (iv) to not have followed any programme of assisted reproduction, (v) to wish to deliver in the reference hospital and (vi) to have no communication problems.
